      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Ellipses, parabolas, and hyperbolas are all defined as the intersection of a plane with a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "double-napped cone. Circles are considered a special case of ellipses, where the foci (plural for",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "focus, aka centers) are equal. Rectangular hyperbolas are a special case of degenerate hyperbolas,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "where the focus is at the origin.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Ellipses",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Ellipses",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Graph_Ellipse",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This is the standard form of an ellipse. The major difference from ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/1.2-Circles",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " are that ellipses have two radii:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$a$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", the horizontal radius, is the distance from the center to the rightmost point of the ellipse",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$b$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", the vertical radius, is the distance from the center to the topmost point of the ellipse",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Ellipses are always symmetrical about the x-axis and y-axis, taking its center as the origin. This means that there are no “diagonal” ellipses with this form.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Standard-Form",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Standard Form",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The standard form of an ellipse is:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\frac{x^2}{a^2} + \\frac{y^2}{b^2} = 1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "where:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$a$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the horizontal radius",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$b$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the vertical radius",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note how, if ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is equal to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$b$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", the ellipse is a circle with radius ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$b$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\frac{x^2}{a^2} + \\frac{y^2}{a^2} = 1",
            "",
            "\\frac{x^2 + y^2}{a^2} = 1",
            "",
            "x^2 + y^2 = a^2"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The standard form of an ellipse with its center, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$(\\alpha, \\beta)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\frac{(x - \\alpha)^2}{a^2} + \\frac{(y - \\beta)^2}{b^2} = 1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Deriving-the-Standard-Form",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Deriving the Standard Form",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Consider two points, A and B, with cartesian coordinates ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$(c, 0)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$(-c, 0)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", respectively. The",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "distance from A to B is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$2c$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". A curve has a property such that for any point ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$P$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on the curve, the sum",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "of the distances from ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$P$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to A and B is a constant ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$2a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Graph_Ellipse Derivation",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To derive the standard form of an ellipse, we first use the distance formula to mathematically express",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the sum-of-distances property:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "|PB|^2 = R_1^2 = y^2 + (x + c)^2",
            "|PA|^2 = R_2^2 = y^2 + (x - c)^2",
            "R_1 + R_2 = 2a \\quad \\textrm{(1)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "where we define PB and PA as ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", just to refer to them in a simple way. That is simply the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "pythagoras theorem. We then manipulate the equations to obtain the difference of squares of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "R_1^2 - R_2^2 = [(x+c)^2 + y^2] - [(x-c)^2 + y^2]",
            "= (x+c)^2 - (x-c)^2",
            "= (x^2 + 2xc + c^2) - (x^2 - 2xc + c^2)",
            "= 4cx \\quad \\textrm{(2)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Using the difference of squares formula, we can express this as:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "R_1^2 - R_2^2 = 4cx = (R_1 + R_2)(R_1 - R_2)",
            "= (2a)(R_1 - R_2)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We can hence calculate ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_1 - R_2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "R_1 - R_2 = \\frac{R_1^2 - R_2^2}{2a} = \\frac{4cx}{2a} = \\frac{2cx}{a} \\quad \\textrm{(3)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Then sum the two equations ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "(1)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "(3)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to obtain a value for ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "(R_1 + R_2) + (R_1 - R_2) = 2a + \\frac{2cx}{a}",
            "2R_1 = 2a + \\frac{2cx}{a}",
            "R_1 = a + \\frac{cx}{a}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We can use the value of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$R_1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to obtain an equation",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "R_1 = a + \\frac{cx}{a}",
            "\\sqrt{y^2 + (x+c)^2} = a + \\frac{cx}{a}",
            "\\text{Squaring both sides,}",
            "y^2 + (x+c)^2 = (a + \\frac{cx}{a})^2",
            "y^2 + x^2 + c^2 + 2cx = a^2 + \\frac{c^2x^2}{a^2} + 2cx",
            "y^2 + x^2 + c^2 = a^2 + \\frac{c^2x^2}{a^2}",
            "x^2(1-\\frac{c^2}{a^2}) + y^2 = a^2 - c^2"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "And finally simplify to obtain the standard form:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "x^2(1-\\frac{c^2}{a^2}) + y^2 = a^2 - c^2",
            "",
            "x^2(\\frac{a^2 - c^2}{a^2}) + y^2 = a^2 - c^2",
            "",
            "\\frac{x^2}{a^2} + \\frac{y^2}{a^2 - c^2} = 1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If we define ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$b$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to be equal to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$a^2 - c^2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", we can express the standard form as:",
